  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Republic of the Marshall Islands: Baseline Survey Contributing to Addressing Climate Vulnerability in the Water Sector</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the face of increasing climate risks including more frequent and extreme droughts, the Republic of the Marshall Islands (RMI) requires greater investment in water related efforts. The project is a small component of the larger UNDP Addressing Climate Vulnerability in the Water Sector (ACWA) in the Marshall Islands project currently in its initial stages. The 7-year project (2019-2026) is originally funded by the Green Climate Fund (GCF) and implemented by UNDP. The RMI Baseline Survey Project will contribute to RMI&apos;s ability to adapt to increasing climate risks, particularly droughts, by conducting surveys to substantiate baselines to reflect the community demographics and rainwater harvesting system quality in communities and validate information gaps between the ACWA project formulation and implementation. IOM will work in close coordination with UNDP and the RMI Environment Protection Agency (EPA) throughout the project.</narrative>
  </description>
